properties.Title: Extreme Cold Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A prolonged period of very cold wind chills is expected. Temperatures near -40 and moderate northwesterly winds are expected to give wind chill values near -55 tonight and tomorrow morning. As the wind weakens tomorrow afternoon, the wind chill is expected to moderate. ### Extreme cold puts everyone at risk. Risks are greater for young children, older adults, people with chronic illnesses, people working or exercising outdoors, and those without proper shelter. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Title: Freezing Rain Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Freezing rain is expected or occurring. Freezing rain has developed and will continue to spread eastwards throughout the night. After the freezing rain, snow is forecast to fall on top of the ice covered surfaces. Freezing rain was reported west of Benalto at 8:45 PM MST. ### Surfaces such as highways, roads, walkways and parking lots may become icy and slippery. Freezing rain warnings are issued when rain falling in sub-zero temperatures creates ice build-up and icy surfaces. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ABstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #ABStorm.

properties.Title: Extreme Cold Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A period of very cold wind chills is expected. A cold airmass remains entrenched over the central Arctic. Air temperatures approaching -40C combined with wind speeds up to 20 km/h is expected to produce extreme wind chill values of -55 this evening. Conditions may improve overnight with increased cloud cover. ### Extreme cold puts everyone at risk. Watch for cold related symptoms: shortness of breath, chest pain, muscle pain and weakness, numbness and colour change in fingers and toes. Extreme cold warnings are issued when very cold temperatures or wind chill creates an elevated risk to health such as frost bite and hypothermia. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Title: Snowfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Snowfall with total amounts of 10 to 15 cm is expected. Snow is now falling in Churchill. 10 to 15 cm of accumulation is expected by Wednesday morning. Northerly winds are expected to increase to 40 gusting to 60 km/h overnight, bringing blowing snow with reduced visibilities. Snow will taper off Wednesday morning. ### Rapidly accumulating snow could make travel difficult over some locations. Snowfall warnings are issued when significant snowfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to MBstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #MBStorm.
